$$\implies ||X|| ||Y||cos(\theta)=\frac{1}{2}[||X||^2+||Y||^2-||X-Y||^2]$$

$$||X||||Y||cos(\theta) = \frac{1}{2}(X^TX+Y^TY-(X-Y)^T(X-Y))=\frac{1}{2}(X^TX+Y^TY-X^TX-Y^TY+X^TY+Y^TX)$$

$$=\frac{1}{2}(X^TY+Y^TX)$$

Since $$X^TY=Y^TX$$
$$=\frac{1}{2}(X^TY+X^TY)=\frac{1}{2}(2X^TY)=X^TY$$
	
